  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cash assistance for Vulnerable Households affected by Typhoon Mangkhut ASDSW</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An assessment done by the Humanitarian Response Consortium (HRC) with members A Single Drop of Safe Water (ASDSW)  and Philippine Disaster Risk Reduction Network (PDRRN) with Christian Aid in Cagayan found that farmers, farm workers, and indigenous people are the most vulnerable especially those in remote areas or difficult to access.  In most areas, they have received minimal or no assistance at all from the government.  One IP leader of the Agta community in Brgy. Santa Margarita walked six hours to Baggao to ask for food and blankets but the most pressing need is still access to cash (https://www.rappler.com/nation/212205-agta-leader-marlon-rosalem-walks-6-hours-get-aid-typhoon-ompong).  HRC has link up with Mabuwaya Foundation, who will assist the five sitios of the Agta community in Santa Margarita in Baggao, Cagayan.  Mabuwaya Foundation has been working in the Sierra Madre and with the Agta communities since 2003.  ASDSW will lead the distribution of unconditional cash assistance that will hopefully ease up the stress around food security and enable affacted househols to meet the food security needs.</narrative>
  </description>
